lines.text: You better get home, I don't want your folks to worry.
Henry, you're such an old lady.

[Callie has hitch hiked with a trucker to go to Indiana and just finished having a conversation about where she was going and what she was doing]
Looks like a Cock pit in here.

[The trucker then puts the moves on Callie]
No, that's okay.

[In a sort of high toned voice]
Look don't give me that, I hate kids.

[In a firm voice]
Look, I am not a kid.

[With a smile]
I can see that you're not.
